div.p:
A. The Father is not the Sonne but another person; 
   Ioh. 5. 32. & 8. 16, 17, 18. the Son is not the Father, but another; 
   Ioh. 1. 1. 1 Ioh. 2. 1. Phil. 2. 6. and the Holy Ghost is neither the Father nor the Son, but another; 
   Ioh. 14. 16. & 15. 26. Is. 48. 16. and therefore they are each distinct from other as severall, and distinct Persons.

A. In that he gathereth men into it 
   Psal. 110. 1, 2, 3. Isai 43. 5, 6., appoints Ordinances and Officers unto it 1 Cor. 12. 4. Eph. 4. 11. Mat. 28. 20., and prescribeth laws 
   Iam. 4. 12. Isai 33. 22. for the manner of carrying on all things therein;

A. God doth graciously impute it to us 
   Rom. 4. 6., and faith is the instrument for the receiving of it 
   Rom. 3. 28. & 4. 5. & Gal. 2. 16., that so by it we may be justified;
